## Critical Rules вЂ” NEVER violate these

### 1. No new dependencies
Do NOT add npm packages, CDN libraries, or build tools. The project runs as raw ES modules. Only existing CDN deps: JSZip, browser-image-compression, Material Icons.

### 2. No framework patterns
Do NOT introduce React, Vue, Lit, or any component framework. UI is built with vanilla DOM manipulation and innerHTML strings. Follow the existing pattern.

### 3. Preserve the data-attribute system
HTML в†” JS binding uses `data-*` attributes:
- `data-state-key="paddingPercent"` вЂ” binds input to store key
- `data-function="updateBgColor"` вЂ” calls window[functionName] on click
- `data-action="trigger-file-input"` вЂ” handled by eventHandler.js delegation
- `data-i18n="layout.padding"` вЂ” translation key
- `data-group="paddingPercent"` вЂ” chip group toggle

### 4. Global functions via window
~90 functions are exposed to `window` in main.js `exposeGlobals()`. This is the bridge between HTML data-attributes and JS logic. When adding a new function that HTML needs to call, add it to `exposeGlobals()`.

### 5. Store update flow
```
User interaction в†’ eventHandler.js or data-function
  в†’ window.updateState(key, value)  [main.js]
    в†’ store.setKey(key, value)       [store.js]
      в†’ applyDerivedState()          [store.js вЂ” auto-sync titleв†”subtitle, fonts, legal]
        в†’ store.notify()
          в†’ renderer.render()         [RAF-scheduled]
            в†’ renderToCanvas()        [23-step pipeline on Canvas 2D]
```
**NEVER call store.state directly. Always use setKey() or setState().**

### 6. Rendering pipeline
`renderToCanvas()` in renderer.js is a single ~1900-line function. The drawing order matters:
1. Background (color в†’ gradient в†’ image)
2. Legal pre-calculation (reserves space at bottom)
3. Layout type detection (7 types by aspect ratio)
4. Size multipliers
5. Logo bounds
6. KV for wide formats
7. Text area calculation
8. Text gradient overlay
9. Title в†’ Subtitle
10. KV for vertical formats
11. Legal в†’ Age
12. KV draw в†’ Logo draw
13. Debug overlays в†’ Habr border в†’ Safe area

**When modifying rendering: specify which step(s) you're changing. Do not restructure the order without explicit request.**

### 7. CSS font strings for Canvas
Multi-word font families MUST be quoted: `"YS Text"`, `"Yandex Serif Display"`.
Use `getFontString()` from renderer.js for all Canvas font assignments.

### 8. applyDerivedState() side effects
When changing `titleSize` в†’ `subtitleSize` auto-recalculates (and vice versa).
When changing `fontFamily` в†’ cascades to title/subtitle/legal/age if they matched old value.
When changing `logoLanguage` в†’ legal text auto-switches RUв†”KZ.
When changing `activePairIndex` в†’ title/subtitle/kvSelected/bgImage sync from active pair.
**Always check applyDerivedState() when adding new state keys that depend on other keys.**

